  <Properties>
    <contentGrid>
      <Value><![CDATA[{
  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "0708fc2f-92f1-4efc-a9d1-a755f66e6845",
      "key": "a1111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111105",
      "udi": null,
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e6ac523-7122-4994-9f51-7ca67065222a",
      "key": "a1111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111101",
      "udi": null,
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "dfab01ba-2429-4be9-a894-3c6c4c49df94",
      "key": "a1111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111103",
      "udi": null,
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "image",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": [
            {
              "key": "b2222222-2222-4222-8222-222222222201",
              "mediaKey": "54629230-a4a2-4567-8575-04596a39830b",
              "mediaTypeAlias": "umbracoMediaVectorGraphics",
              "crops": [],
              "focalPoint": null
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f170b29c-338f-4ab8-a5c4-f72c90826f69",
      "key": "a1111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111115",
      "udi": null,
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "a1111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111109",
      "udi": null,
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Introduction"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "An overview of the Navigation - In Page feature and what it provides to content editors and site visitors"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe Navigation - In Page feature creates a sticky sidebar navigation that automatically links to features on the current page. As the visitor scrolls through the content, Bootstrap ScrollSpy highlights the currently visible section in the navigation list, providing a clear sense of position within the page.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis is particularly useful on longer pages where content is broken into distinct sections. Rather than forcing visitors to scroll blindly, the in-page navigation gives them an overview of what the page contains and lets them jump directly to the section they need.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOnly features that have a \u003Cstrong\u003EFeature Title\u003C/strong\u003E set will appear in the navigation picker. Features without a title \u2014 such as standalone images, the navigation block itself, or the page title and description block \u2014 are automatically excluded from the picker. This keeps the navigation clean and focused on meaningful, titled content sections.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "a1111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111",
      "udi": null,
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Sticky Positioning"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "How the navigation stays visible while scrolling and highlights the active section"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe sticky behaviour is entirely content-driven using CSS \u003Ccode\u003E:has(.sticky-nav)\u003C/code\u003E and is controlled by the editor via the \u003Cstrong\u003EEnable Sticky\u003C/strong\u003E toggle in the block settings. When sticky is enabled, the navigation remains visible in the sidebar as the user scrolls through the main content area.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe implementation adapts to different screen sizes. On desktop (md breakpoint and above), the feature items container within the sidebar becomes sticky, keeping the navigation anchored while the main content scrolls. On mobile devices (below the md breakpoint), the entire sidebar area becomes sticky instead, and the navigation list collapses behind a Bootstrap toggler button to save vertical space.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe sticky offset is controlled by the \u003Ccode\u003E--navbar-height\u003C/code\u003E CSS custom property, which defaults to \u003Ccode\u003E7rem\u003C/code\u003E. This same value is used for \u003Ccode\u003Escroll-margin-top\u003C/code\u003E on feature blocks, ensuring that when a visitor clicks a navigation link, the target section scrolls to a position just below the site navbar rather than being hidden behind it.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "a1111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111113",
      "udi": null,
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Feature Title Filtering"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "How the navigation picker decides which features to show and which to exclude"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe navigation picker is powered by a custom Contentment DataSource that scans the current page for all feature blocks across every block grid on the page. It applies a straightforward rule: \u003Cstrong\u003Eonly features that have a Feature Title set are offered in the picker\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis design decision means that content-focused features like Rich Text Editors, FAQs, Tabs, and Code blocks naturally appear in the picker when they have titles, while utility features like standalone images, navigation blocks, and the page title block are excluded because they typically don\u0027t carry a Feature Title.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe beauty of this approach is that it gives content editors implicit control. If you want a feature to be available for in-page navigation, simply give it a Feature Title. If you want to exclude a feature that does have a title, you can either remove its title or simply deselect it in the navigation picker.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "c345e5ce-768f-47e0-968a-e7859dbe0b07",
      "key": "158b5253-8371-4e7a-bb91-9e16a9d3c464",
      "udi": null,
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "1bf0a936-42ed-452d-aff2-017e4ffb8a59",
      "udi": null,
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Mobile Responsive Collapse"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "How the navigation adapts on smaller screens with a collapsible toggler"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EOn mobile devices the full navigation list would take up too much vertical space, so the feature uses Bootstrap\u0027s collapse component to hide the list behind a toggler button. The toggler appears only on screens below the md breakpoint and uses the standard Bootstrap \u003Ccode\u003Enavbar-toggler\u003C/code\u003E pattern for a familiar user experience.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhen the visitor taps the toggler, the navigation list smoothly expands. On desktop screens (md and above), the list is always visible with no toggler shown, using Bootstrap\u0027s \u003Ccode\u003Ed-md-block\u003C/code\u003E utility class to control visibility.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA subtle but important detail: padding is applied to the inner \u003Ccode\u003E\u0026lt;ul\u0026gt;\u003C/code\u003E element rather than the collapsing \u003Ccode\u003E\u0026lt;div\u0026gt;\u003C/code\u003E container. This prevents animation jank that can occur when padding is applied directly to an element that Bootstrap is animating between zero and full height.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "038786dc-d8c9-47d5-ab04-6b395ddf73f7",
      "udi": null,
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Future Enhancements"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Planned improvements and additional options coming to the in-page navigation feature"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe Navigation - In Page feature will continue to evolve with additional options and refinements. Some of the enhancements we are considering include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPer-feature allow toggle\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 A setting on individual feature blocks to explicitly control whether they should be available to in-page navigation, giving editors more granular control beyond the Feature Title rule\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EURL fragment anchors\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 Adding clickable permalink anchors next to feature titles so that visitors can copy and share direct links to specific sections on the page\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAuto-collapse on click\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 On mobile, automatically collapsing the navigation list after a visitor taps a link, so the content area returns to full view\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EElement type exclusion\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 The ability to configure which feature types should never appear in the navigation picker, either through code-level configuration or editor-facing settings on the navigation block\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese enhancements aim to give content editors even more flexibility while keeping the feature straightforward to use. The core principle remains the same: the navigation should work well out of the box with minimal configuration, while offering deeper control for those who need it.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "c4b3a613-0d2c-4470-8d06-f7efea52d6e0",
      "key": "b2fd4288-625d-49c1-b7ee-f38cf74087cd",
